<h3>During the week</h3>
<ul>
    <li>The week was a mixed bag emotionally. Early wins, like the progress on upcoach's new website, scheduling the WeekVista launch and refining strategies for SumBox, were tempered by introspective moments. I had some though conversations, where I shared my struggles. It was a moment of vulnerability but also a reaffirmation of my commitment to transparency and fairness in everything I do.</li>
    <li>On a brighter note, I stumbled upon my old 2019 notebooks and found my 5-year goals. It was an enlightening moment to see that I had completed 3 out of 5 items on the list. While they didn’t turn out exactly as I had envisioned, it reminded me of the power of setting intentions—even when they lack specificity. Inspired by this, I’ve begun crafting my 2025 vision and next 5-year plans. The process has been eye-opening, energizing, and just plain fun. Exercises like this are why I love reflecting and planning—it’s incredible to see how far I’ve come and where I want to go.
